              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a bright-eyed, chubby-cheeked 2-year-old girl from Brno, Czech Republic, who is usually full of energy and loves playing with her toy animals and stacking blocks. She attends a local toddler daycare group three mornings per week, where she happily interacts with other children her age. She lives at home with her parents and a 5-year-old brother in a modern apartment.\n\nOver the past four days, {patientName} has been noticeably unwell. She developed a persistent, rattly cough [MEDDIALOG:J18.9:0] and a high fever [SNOMED:J18.9], with her temperature reaching 38.9 °C. She has been breathing rapidly and visibly working harder than usual to breathe, her small nostrils flaring with each breath [SNOMED:J18.9]. She has been irritable, refusing most solid foods, and clinging to her mother. Her parents noted that she seemed unusually tired and lethargic [SNOMED:J18.9].\n\nAt the emergency paediatric visit, {patientName} appeared flushed and moderately distressed. Her oxygen saturation on room air was 93%, indicating hypoxia [SNOMED:J18.9]. Auscultation revealed coarse crackles in the right lower lobe. She had a runny nose at the beginning of her illness, and her parents recalled a mild upper respiratory infection in her brother the previous week. A chest X-ray was ordered to evaluate the extent of the lung infection [MEDDIALOG:J18.9:0, MEDDIALOG:J18.9:1]."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:2c8d93b4-4472-496c-9412-fa4b5d999bb6",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
        "text": {
          "status": "generated",
          "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">patient-history</div>"
        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} was born at term via spontaneous vaginal delivery with no neonatal complications. She has been meeting all developmental milestones appropriately. She received her standard Czech immunisation schedule vaccinations, including pneumococcal conjugate vaccine. She has no known chronic illness or prior hospitalisations.\n\n{patientName} attends a toddler daycare group, which increases her exposure to respiratory pathogens [MEDDIALOG:J18.9:0]. Her brother had a mild upper respiratory tract infection the week prior to her current presentation, suggesting a possible infectious source within the household. {patientName} has no history of recurrent respiratory infections, and there is no known history of asthma or atopy. She has no documented surgical history and no current regular medications prior to this illness. She has a known allergy to penicillin (urticaria)."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
